Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.11,0:00:19.44,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Piercing through the Macro sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.81,0:00:25.26,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,a thunderbolt strikes the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.54,0:00:31.01,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,To awaken us, the young mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.22,0:00:37.21,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,the Light struck
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.53,0:00:43.28,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Macross! Macross!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.55,0:00:49.02,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,The brave youths who arise
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.28,0:00:53.13,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,and fight to protect their loved ones
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.42,0:00:58.23,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Will set out on their journey\Nas the war rages on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.50,0:01:01.49,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you love me tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.73,0:01:06.86,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Slicing through the darkness they fly toward
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.18,0:01:12.88,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,That blue planet that shines in the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.16,0:01:18.37,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Macross! Macross!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.20,0:01:24.50,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Macross!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.25,0:01:39.05,narration,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The conflict between Max and Milia\Nhas ended in marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.82,0:01:45.49,narration,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This, however, has plunged\NBritai's fleet into chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.11,0:01:51.04,signM,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(69,138)}MESSENGER
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.23,0:01:58.92,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A single enemy ship is approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.43,0:02:03.50,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Move the main cannon into firing position.\NTarget the approaching enemy ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.99,0:02:06.05,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!\NMain cannon, lock on target!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.09,0:02:09.86,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The main cannon is standing by to fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.23,0:02:11.51,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Target lock acquired!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.32,0:02:16.21,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they want to settle this one-on-one!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.48,0:02:19.60,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid.\NWhy would they do something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.07,0:02:22.40,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it happens in comic books all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.67,0:02:23.86,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.70,0:02:26.84,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you have to call me\Nan idiot all the time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.58,0:02:28.16,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HFFFFFF&}Please delay firing the main cannon!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.66,0:02:31.00,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting a transmission from the enemy vessel.\NThey request a cease-fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.12,0:02:31.68,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.20,0:02:36.78,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I put it on the speaker?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.10,0:02:43.91,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The approaching vessel does not intend\Nto attack. We request a cease-fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.90,0:03:02.23,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy fighters closing in fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.34,0:03:03.60,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are they up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.20,0:03:15.52,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.91,0:03:19.51,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're interfering with our negotiations.\NJust stay out of the way and watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.95,0:03:22.94,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We can beat them!\NWhy do we need a cease-fire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.47,0:03:27.14,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't negotiate a cease-fire,\Nthe fleet will tear itself apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.84,0:03:29.00,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Preposterous!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.25,0:03:30.63,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.01,0:03:51.79,narration,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A peace envoy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.05,0:03:55.58,narration,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Culture shock may have hit them\Nharder than we thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.91,0:04:11.77,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Leader! It sure feels strange escorting\Nan enemy pod, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.43,0:04:13.63,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You got that right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.19,0:04:15.72,narration,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder who's inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.89,0:04:32.19,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey there!\NWhat are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.27,0:04:34.12,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't climb down by myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.38,0:04:36.72,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, forgive me, sir!\NI didn't mean to...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.57,0:04:43.30,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,These miclone bodies are\Nso weak and powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.66,0:04:49.46,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So this is how we look to them, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.41,0:05:06.76,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome aboard. I'm Colonel Maistroff,\NUN Forces, Strategic Space Command.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.80,0:05:11.60,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I beg your pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.77,0:05:13.50,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a sign of friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.24,0:05:21.69,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am Exsedol, Zentradi {\i1}Zem{\i0}\N1st Class, Chief Archivist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.00,0:05:24.17,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Archivist, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.36,0:05:25.49,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.17,0:05:28.26,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, if you'll follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.30,0:05:34.22,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Archivist Exsedol, I would ask that\Nthis gentleman remain here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.39,0:05:37.27,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You wait here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.79,0:05:38.71,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.25,0:05:41.67,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Be good hosts and get him something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.01,0:05:42.80,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.01,0:05:42.80,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HFFFFFF&}Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.13,0:05:55.56,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Be good hosts and get him something to eat"...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.23,0:05:59.15,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How much could this guy put away?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.39,0:06:03.23,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask me! Anyway, let's bring him\Na container or something to sit on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.88,0:06:19.41,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And what might that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.75,0:06:21.48,SMacross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They sell electronic goods there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.80,0:06:25.21,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And use "money" to conduct "business," correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.50,0:06:26.64,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're certainly well-informed!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.71,0:06:32.85,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.52,0:06:35.40,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It gave me quite a shock!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.63,0:06:40.35,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that would take a lot of explaining,\Nso perhaps some other time...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.75,0:06:45.46,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, a military secret, eh?\NI see, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.98,0:06:49.71,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And what is that translucent uniform?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.77,0:06:51.94,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, umm... that's a\Nmilitary secret too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.84,0:06:58.81,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The ambassador has entered\Nthe conference room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.10,0:07:00.82,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Understood. I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.37,0:07:02.68,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What about the enemy ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.09,0:07:04.26,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No change whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.61,0:07:05.99,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maintain our current status.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.49,0:07:07.19,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Claudia!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.62,0:07:08.14,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.20,0:07:11.45,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you.\NIf they make any hostile moves...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.42,0:07:13.19,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,then shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.46,0:07:14.18,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.30,0:07:34.20,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.24,0:07:42.19,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.10,0:07:44.56,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then please have another.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.50,0:07:46.49,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.08,0:07:49.90,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The concerned parties still aren't here yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.29,0:07:55.06,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, sir. After all, they were on\Ncombat duty when we called them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.78,0:08:03.11,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Milia!\N1st Flight Commander Milia!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.47,0:08:06.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Archivist Exsedol!\NExcellency!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.10,0:08:09.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That wedding business caused a\Nrather astonishing commotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.30,0:08:12.49,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!\NEven I had no idea
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.99,0:08:14.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,that things would turn out like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.92,0:08:18.17,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Or that I would be here either, I'll bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.32,0:08:19.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.02,0:08:23.02,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And this is the male\Nyou've mated with?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.63,0:08:25.07,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.\NThat's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.36,0:08:26.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Mated with"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.16,0:08:29.17,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Reporting for duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.05,0:08:32.91,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Max, what's with that face?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.01,0:08:33.90,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.10,0:08:37.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Being micloned, I didn't recognize you at first
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.91,0:08:39.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,but you're one of the prisoners\Nfrom the main fleet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.41,0:08:41.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're that...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.96,0:08:45.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Our positions are much different now.\NHow did you escape us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.33,0:08:47.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Was it the power of Protoculture?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.99,0:08:49.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how to answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.99,0:08:53.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Another military secret, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.72,0:08:55.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Warera Nantes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.96,0:08:57.27,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Conda Bromco...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.58,0:08:58.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Loli Dosel...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.25,0:09:06.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Exsedol!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.69,0:09:10.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see the masterminds behind our\NProtoculture-shock are all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.92,0:09:12.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We, that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.98,0:09:14.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That is to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.70,0:09:16.35,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To say we, uh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.51,0:09:19.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Relax, nothing's going to\Nhappen to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.96,0:09:25.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, Archivist Exsedol,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.16,0:09:28.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,would you please tell us the reason\Nfor this meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.16,0:09:42.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Two vitally important people\Nare not yet present.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.41,0:09:46.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They are the reason that things\Nhave come to this:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.33,0:09:49.50,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The superhuman Shao Pai Long,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.70,0:09:51.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,and the woman who is at the core\Nof your psychological attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.21,0:09:53.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Shao Pai Long"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.59,0:09:55.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He means that movie!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.74,0:09:57.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like they thought those\Nwere real super powers!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.97,0:10:00.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite a misunderstanding!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.23,0:10:03.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But what about this "psychological attack"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.26,0:10:08.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know of anyone who could be at\N"the core of a psychological attack."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.83,0:10:11.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Could you perhaps be more specific?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.84,0:10:14.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A person of that magnitude isn't\Nconsidered important?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.31,0:10:17.07,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It must be Protoculture, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.05,0:10:18.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.72,0:10:19.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Could he mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.55,0:10:20.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.48,0:10:21.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What I mean is:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.40,0:10:26.07,songM,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Whoosh, whoosh! Whoosh, whoosh!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.20,0:10:29.71,songM,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"My boyfriend is a pilot"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.71,0:10:27.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Minmay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.81,0:10:29.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We knew it!\NLynn Minmay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.00,0:10:33.42,songM,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Shining, making a rapid descent"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.59,0:10:35.90,songM,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Whoosh, whoosh! Whoosh!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.06,0:10:39.16,songM,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Then BOOM! he makes a sudden climb"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.15,0:10:40.70,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I thought as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.39,0:10:40.74,songM,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Leaving a long..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.12,0:10:43.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who would've thought that a song\Ncould have such an effect?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.61,0:10:44.41,songM,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Whoosh, whoosh! Whoosh, whoosh!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.48,0:10:45.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Make arrangements at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.86,0:10:46.56,songM,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Plane..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.81,0:10:52.71,narration,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Minmay...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.98,0:11:00.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, what were we called here for?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.97,0:11:03.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's just another example of\Nmilitary being self-centered!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.49,0:11:05.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They never think about us civilians!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.19,0:11:07.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I will not...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.22,0:11:09.96,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Lynn Kaifun!\NWe are in the middle of negotiations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.22,0:11:12.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is not the place for you to\Nbe giving your speeches.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.29,0:11:16.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, you are not to repeat\Nwhat you see or hear here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.41,0:11:17.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.28,0:11:18.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.38,0:11:22.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You might be able to accomplish\Nwhat you've always wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.82,0:11:24.05,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We should cooperate with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.62,0:11:28.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone you requested is now here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.58,0:11:30.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.90,0:11:44.86,narration,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I certainly hope we can negotiate\Nwith the Zentradi, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.81,0:12:15.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Have you gotten the hang of\Nthings here, Captain Hayase?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.43,0:12:17.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.29,0:12:22.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They say the Macross has entered into\Na cease-fire with the Zentradi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.29,0:12:23.49,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.92,0:12:28.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If it holds, we might not have to\Nuse the Grand Cannon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.51,0:12:30.02,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt that will be the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.61,0:12:36.27,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The report says that the cease-fire is only with\Nthat part of the fleet that's already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.85,0:12:39.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, we'll\Nprobably use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.07,0:12:44.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be in the central core.\NIf you need anything, come see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.82,0:13:00.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lynn Kaifun, what is your rank?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.05,0:13:02.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a civilian.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.66,0:13:05.91,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A civilian?! You, a warrior with\Nsuch superhuman abilities?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.37,0:13:08.17,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have no superhuman abilities!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.25,0:13:08.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.68,0:13:14.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be honest with you.\NYou'll find out eventually anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.00,0:13:18.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We do not possess the supernatural\Npowers you've attributed to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.37,0:13:20.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But that man's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.34,0:13:23.02,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That was a form of entertainment\Nwe call a "movie."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.12,0:13:26.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But what about the destructive power\Nof the Macross's energy field?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.47,0:13:29.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I assume you mean the barrier and\Nthe explosion that occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.33,0:13:31.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That was purely\Ntechnological in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.58,0:13:32.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.29,0:13:35.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How can this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.82,0:13:39.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But you cannot deny the\Npower of that song!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.49,0:13:40.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The power of that song?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.34,0:13:44.27,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Excellency!\NThat's the real thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.61,0:13:47.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've been deeply moved by the\Npower of the songs!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.87,0:13:52.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, those who encountered\Nthe Protoculture
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.83,0:13:55.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,were drained of their will\Nto fight by song.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.87,0:13:59.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They awakened to culture and\Nthey were destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.79,0:14:01.13,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.35,0:14:08.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To us Zentradi, warfare is life and our\Nhistory is one of battle after battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.29,0:14:10.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But once again we have met with culture,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.74,0:14:15.02,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,and the shock of this has made our\Nsoldiers begin to reject warfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.32,0:14:18.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So as to avoid the mistakes\Nof our predecessors,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.04,0:14:21.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Bodolzaa, supreme commander\Nof the main fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.28,0:14:24.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,has ordered that ours is the only\Nfleet to have contact with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.00,0:14:26.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, if he learns of these results,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.71,0:14:30.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,the main fleet will most likely\Nlaunch an all-out attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.23,0:14:32.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To wipe out Earth's\nculture, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.06,0:14:34.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The main fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.12,0:14:37.49,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The large fleet mentioned in your report?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.79,0:14:38.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.32,0:14:43.16,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Britai, what is the meaning\Nof this cease-fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.33,0:14:47.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think our fleet can fight the\NMacross in the shape we're in?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.44,0:14:52.27,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, this will all be settled\Nonce the main fleet arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.70,0:14:53.95,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The main fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.31,0:14:56.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you, Lap'Lamiz, you didn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.35,0:14:58.61,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have reported everything to Lord Bodolzaa.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.96,0:15:02.39,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He decided to mobilize the main fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.10,0:15:06.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So he has determined that the people\Nof Earth are the Protoculture?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.07,0:15:07.73,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.82,0:15:09.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.97,0:15:12.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This fleet will be destroyed\Nalong with the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.65,0:15:14.49,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Preposterous!\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.10,0:15:17.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Because we've been contaminated\Nby the Protoculture.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.68,0:15:18.78,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.39,0:15:21.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What was that, Lord?\NIs that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.81,0:15:23.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.82,0:15:27.50,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then our fleet will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.05,0:15:29.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.47,0:15:36.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder, would the Macross alone\Nchoose to flee the Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.34,0:15:38.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You want us to abandon the Earth?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.34,0:15:39.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.34,0:15:40.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We could never agree to that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.37,0:15:45.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Macross is a warship, part of the\NEarth UN Forces, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.43,0:15:47.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HFFFFFF&}Yes, that is the answer I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.79,0:15:50.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As it would prove rather difficult\Nfor our fleet to escape,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.73,0:15:53.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,it seems that we will be facing\Na common enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.46,0:15:54.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?!\NWhat do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.44,0:15:59.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have just received word that the main\Nfleet is headed for this star system.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.19,0:16:01.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The main fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.27,0:16:07.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Bodol main fleet, which consists\Nof 4,790,122 warships,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.40,0:16:10.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,has finally been mobilized.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.54,0:16:14.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like we need to prepare ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.93,0:16:20.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We may have to trust to fate whether\Nor not the Earth will survive, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.32,0:16:21.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We'll do everything we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.73,0:16:23.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You must be joking!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.13,0:16:25.59,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Five million ships?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.33,0:16:28.56,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's over.\NThis is hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.32,0:16:32.62,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Milia, we may die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.08,0:16:37.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Max, nothing would be greater than\Ndying together in combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.81,0:16:39.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Together...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.86,0:16:46.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is not the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.60,0:16:47.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.36,0:16:54.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Macross has fought us off\Nsingle-handedly, has it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.72,0:16:57.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There is no guarantee of victory,\Nbut we have a way to fight them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.18,0:17:04.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I hear they've even called in the reserves!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.41,0:17:07.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Man, there goes my leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.27,0:17:10.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Zentradi have a pretty big fleet, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.35,0:17:13.91,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So what?\NWe got the Grand Cannon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.62,0:17:32.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.79,0:17:34.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Admiral!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.41,0:17:37.08,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Misa!\NVery well, this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.38,0:17:45.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.01,0:17:47.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What will happen to the Macross?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.80,0:17:49.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It probably won't survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.80,0:17:54.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Before long, we'll have to use it to\Ndivert the enemy's attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.47,0:17:55.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.67,0:17:57.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It may be cruel, but there's no other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.02,0:18:00.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Father, I have something to ask of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.05,0:18:02.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.40,0:18:04.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please send me back to the Macross.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.88,0:18:06.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.82,0:18:08.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I want to stand with my comrades.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.68,0:18:10.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've fought this far side by side!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.52,0:18:13.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You ought to be able\Nto do it, Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.18,0:18:16.74,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You want to go that badly?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.87,0:18:18.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!\NSo you'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.54,0:18:19.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.95,0:18:21.05,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.35,0:18:22.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.84,0:18:26.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot send my only beloved\Ndaughter to certain death!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.11,0:18:28.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way I could let you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.80,0:18:30.07,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.17,0:18:31.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So am I.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.17,0:18:32.70,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then transfer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.22,0:18:35.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, I'm also a father.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.43,0:18:38.50,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll throw you in\Nthe brig if I have to!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.29,0:18:49.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you two intend to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.02,0:18:50.94,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.37,0:18:56.00,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Bodolzaa probably intends to\Ndestroy our fleet as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.31,0:18:59.00,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's no other choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.80,0:19:02.89,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It seems I must walk the same path as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.97,0:19:04.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lap'Lamiz...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.47,0:19:06.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do not die in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.07,0:19:08.99,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You either, Britai.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.22,0:19:11.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, Kamujin?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.80,0:19:14.30,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count me out.\NThere's no way you can win.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.58,0:19:17.18,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I can't stomach the thought\Nof helping the Macross.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.48,0:19:20.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, I wasn't counting\Non your help anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.46,0:19:22.01,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?\NOh, is that so?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.04,0:19:24.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.04,0:19:25.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.07,0:19:28.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Anywhere.\NSet whatever coordinates you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.37,0:19:30.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Kamujin...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.61,0:19:31.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.87,0:19:32.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.94,0:19:34.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn right.\NLet's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.13,0:19:51.73,narration,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Bodolzaa, I will show you how\NBritai Kridanik fights his last battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.69,0:20:00.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In many cases, branch fleets are ordered to\Nretreat should their flagship be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.01,0:20:02.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.57,0:20:03.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,One more thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.74,0:20:06.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Within the branch fleets, only\NBelnar-class flagships,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.05,0:20:10.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,that is, ships occupying one of\Nthe top three ranks,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.48,0:20:13.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,are informed of the position\Nof the rest of the fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.61,0:20:17.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see, so we "crush the head of\Nthe snake," is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.32,0:20:20.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's still more than 2,000\Nheavy warships to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.46,0:20:26.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, will the Earth join our thousand ships\Nto fight an enemy of 4.8 million?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.41,0:20:28.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Archivist Exsedol...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.11,0:20:33.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Such is the consensus of our\NProtoculture-contaminated fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.43,0:20:44.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Minmay, your songs have\Nshaken us to our very core.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.07,0:20:47.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.03,0:20:51.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Soon we will face the main fleet in\Na battle that is both unavoidable
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.72,0:20:53.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,and in all probability quite ferocious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.85,0:21:00.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We may never again be able to listen to\Nand be moved by your songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.11,0:21:05.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Minmay, would you sing for us here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.81,0:21:07.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.13,0:21:17.11,songM2,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Whoosh, whoosh! Whoosh, whoosh!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.28,0:21:21.80,songM2,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My boyfriend is a pilot
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.67,0:21:25.47,songM2,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shining, making a rapid descent
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.96,0:21:29.00,songM2,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then BOOM! he makes a sudden climb
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.46,0:21:34.78,songM2,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Leaving a long trail of vapor
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.29,0:21:41.01,songM2,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He traces two big hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.85,0:21:48.30,songM2,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A love sign in the big, blue sky
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.73,0:21:51.84,songM2,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"I love you, you love me?"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.67,0:21:56.40,songM2,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But he's head over heels
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.79,0:22:02.25,songM2,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For his plane instead of me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.00,0:22:06.02,songM2,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Whoosh, whoosh! Whoosh, whoosh!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.42,0:22:13.02,songM2,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My boyfriend is a pilot
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.25,0:22:23.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Multiple de-fold signatures detected!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.87,0:22:25.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.46,0:22:26.84,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Detecting suspected de-folds:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.94,0:22:29.41,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Multiple gravitational anomalies\Nand luminescent phenomena!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.83,0:22:28.54,MacrossCollide,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.41,0:22:31.56,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The signatures are increasing in number!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.05,0:22:51.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The readings are too strong.\NWe're unable to calculate!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.98,0:22:54.38,Macross1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,De-fold readings are off the scale!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.40,0:22:58.07,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The main fleet!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.41,0:23:34.91,signM,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(78,109)}Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.41,0:23:34.91,signM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(301,450)}Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.89,0:23:42.42,narration,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nearly five million ships under\NBodolzaa's command
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.72,0:23:44.89,narration,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,have completely encircled the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.06,0:23:48.00,narration,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All peaceful avenues of resolution\Nhave been closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.03,0:23:53.81,narration,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hikaru bids Minmay farewell and\Nheads off for the final battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.32,0:23:57.74,narration,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Super Dimension\NFortress Macross:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.44,0:24:02.45,signM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(82,152)}Love Drifts Away
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.15,0:24:01.90,narration,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Love Drifts Away"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.59,0:24:23.28,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't follow it anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.52,0:24:29.89,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,The shadow you cast as you run away
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.18,0:24:36.54,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,We all keep running to the end
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.75,0:24:44.20,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,But we still can't see the goal
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.56,0:24:51.00,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,What awaits us after today?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.29,0:24:56.78,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,What awaits us beyond tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.12,0:25:04.36,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Even now, I keep running toward
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.71,0:25:15.50,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,The light that shines so far away
